license: MIT
keywords:
  - Zarankiewicz problem
  - extremal combinatorics
  - K3,3-free bipartite graph
  - formal verification
  - SAT certificates
abstract: >-
  A human-readable proof that Z(9,23,3,3)=103, accompanied by an explicit
  extremal matrix, independent verifiers, exact arithmetic certificates,
  deterministic SAT/MIP models, a Lean arithmetic audit, and a literature review.
